---
@version: [2, current]
@description: Set HTTP headers.
@lot:
- void
- int $status
- string $key = null, string $value = null
- string $value
- array $values
@static: 1
@example: |
  // Get current HTTP header(s)
  test(HTTP::header());
  // Set current HTTP status
  HTTP::header(404);
  // Set current HTTP header(s)
  HTTP::header('Content-Type', 'text/html');
  HTTP::header('Content-Type: text/html');
  HTTP::header([
      'Content-Type' => 'text/html',
      'Content-Length' => 1024
  ]);
...

To remove one or more HTTP headers, set the header value to `false`:

~~~ .php
// Remove all HTTP header(s)
HTTP::header(false);
// Remove `Content-Type`
HTTP::header('Content-Type', false);
// Remove `Content-Type` and `Content-Length`
HTTP::header([
    'Content-Type' => false,
    'Content-Length' => false
]);
~~~